Use the OS default font rendering mode. This selects either [[FontRenderingMode.HintedSmooth]] or.
[[FontRenderingMode.HintedRaster]] on Windows, and either [[FontRenderingMode.Smooth]] or
[[FontRenderingMode.HintedRaster]] on Mac OS X, depending on the system preferences. This mode
is only available for dynamic fonts, as static fonts are generated at build time.